  "body": "This bug is just a request for us to update the documentation for BytesToAddress. Currently it says \r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/bf1e2631281e1e439533f2abcf1e99a7b2f9552a/common/types.go#L201-L207\r\n\r\nit promises to panic when len(b) > len(a) ie AddressLength. However, as we see in the code above, it actually offsets AddressLength from the end of b when that condition matches.\r\n\r\nCould we perhaps update this?\r\nI noticed this while working on the tests for @tendermint libraries\r\n\r\nPS: here is a test to visualize the responses and check that we don't regress if that comment is retained https://gist.github.com/odeke-em/6f7daa88ac72f83fdfa2e6f5c9ff7a97 or inlined in code\r\n```go\r\npackage address_test\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"bytes\"\r\n\t\"testing\"\r\n\r\n\t\"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/common\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunc TestBytestoAddress(t *testing.T) {\r\n\ttests := [...]struct {\r\n\t\tb         []byte\r\n\t\twantPanic bool\r\n\t}{\r\n\t\t0: {\r\n\t\t\tb: bytes.Join([][]byte{\r\n\t\t\t\t[]byte(\"foo\"),\r\n\t\t\t\tbytes.Repeat([]byte(\"a\"), common.AddressLength/2),\r\n\t\t\t\tbytes.Repeat([]byte(\"z\"), common.AddressLength/2),\r\n\t\t\t\t[]byte(\"b\"),\r\n\t\t\t}, []byte(\"\")),\r\n\t\t\twantPanic: true,\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t\t1: {\r\n\t\t\tb: []byte(\"ethereum\"),\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfor i, tt := range tests {\r\n\t\taddr, res := runBytestoAddress(tt.b)\r\n\t\tgotPanic := res != nil\r\n\t\tif tt.wantPanic != gotPanic {\r\n\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"#%d gotPanic=(%v) wantPanic=(%v)\", i, gotPanic, tt.wantPanic)\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tt.Logf(\"#%d=>\\naddr=%q\\nb   =%q\\naddLen=%d commonLen=%d\", i, addr, tt.b, len(addr), common.AddressLength)\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc runBytestoAddress(b []byte) (addr common.Address, err interface{}) {\r\n\tdefer func() {\r\n\t\terr = recover()\r\n\t}()\r\n\r\n\taddr = common.BytesToAddress(b)\r\n\treturn addr, err\r\n}\r\n```",
